text: The Preventative Coup of November 11 were military events in Brazil. They were done by Henrique Teixeira Lott. The coup led to Nereu Ramos becoming the president until he was succeeded by Juscelino Kubitschek. The coup had no injuries or deaths and peacefully removed Carlos Luz from being president. The tensions led to Brazil having three presidents in one week. == References == Category:Revolutions Category:History of Brazil
title: Preventative Coup of November 11
